<item>
            <title>[JDK-8324280] RISC-V: Incorrect implementation in VM_Version::parse_satp_mode</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8324280</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Currently, method VM_Version::os_uarch_additional_features uses &amp;quot;fgets&amp;quot; to read the contents of /proc/cpuinfo, then calls &amp;quot;parse_satp_mode&amp;quot; with a string with the leading &amp;quot;mmu&amp;quot; and whitespaces removed, like &amp;quot;: sv39\n&amp;quot;. However, &amp;quot;parse_satp_mode&amp;quot; compares this string directly to &amp;quot;sv39&amp;quot;, which always fails and returns VM_MBARE.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Xing Qizheng(@MaxXSoft) will own this issue.</description>
